title: FC Cincinnati tryouts registration exceeds capacity
text:
FC Cincinnati tryouts registration exceeds capacity 
Updated: Wed, Oct 07 2015, 09:29 PM 
CINCINNATI (WKRC) -- There's plenty of interest in Cincinnati's new pro soccer franchise from potential players. FC Cincinnati has tryouts for November 2015, and so many players have registered the team is over capacity. So tryout registration has been closed.The team is scheduled to begin games spring 2016. The team will play at Nippert Stadium.Wednesday evening, Oct. 7, FC Cincinnati revealed its first major sponsors, including the jersey sponsor. 
The first four major sponsors of the team are: Presenting-sponsor of FC Cincinnati: UC Health Jersey Sponsor: Toyota Youth Sponsor: UDF College Supporter Sponsor: Legion Logistics 
John Harkes, a veteran of Major League Soccer and the US National team, was named head coach.
